radiographic_examinations.findings: The gallbladder is distended measuring 3.8 cm in transverse and 7.9 cm in craniocaudal dimension. There is gallbladder wall edema and probable trace pericholecystic fluid. No gallstones are present in the gallbladder. There are hypodensities in bilateral kidneys likely representing simple cysts. A hypodense lesion in the left lobe of the liver suggestive of a hemangioma. No free air or free fluid in the abdomen or pelvis.
